      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) SAR REASONING (why these features matter for hERG)\n- **Protonated amine**: hERG blockers often rely on a **positively charged nitrogen** to engage in electrostatic interactions and/or stabilize binding within the channel cavity (notably near residues that favor cation\u2013\u03c0 / electrostatic interactions).\n- **Aromatic/hydrophobic bulk**: the **phenyl + pyridyl rings** provide **\u03c0-surfaces and hydrophobic contact area** that typically increase affinity to the largely hydrophobic inner cavity of hERG.\n- **Spacing/geometry**: the **~3-atom tether (CCO)** between the cation and the bulky aromatic region is within the common spacing range that allows the cation to sit deeper while the aromatics occupy hydrophobic pockets.  \n- **Conformational flexibility**: enough flexibility to adopt binding-competent conformations, but also a **bulky \u201canchor\u201d** (diaryl tertiary center) that can enhance residence in the cavity.",
