      "content": "Counter-consideration:\n- The **pyridine N** can slightly reduce hydrophobicity and may alter \u03c0-stacking vs phenyl, but it remains aromatic and typically still compatible with hERG binding. Also, the pyridine is **not protonated** here (the amine is already cationic), so you still have one strong cationic center.",
