      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 3) MECHANISTIC BASIS (how it would interact with hERG)\nCanonical hERG blockers often bind in the **central cavity** and interact with aromatic residues (classically **Tyr/Phe** residues) through **\u03c0\u2013\u03c0 and cation\u2013\u03c0 interactions**, while hydrophobic groups occupy lipophilic regions.  \nThis molecule plausibly:\n- Uses the **dimethylammonium** as the **cationic interaction point** (electrostatic/cation\u2013\u03c0 stabilization),\n- Uses the **two aromatic rings** to form **\u03c0/hydrophobic contacts**,\n- Uses the **ether-linked bulky tertiary center** to position the rings and fill the cavity.",
